In [[telecommunication]], the term '''proration''' has the following meanings: 

'''1.'''  The proportional distribution or allocation of parameters, such as [[noise power]] and [[transmission (telecommunications)|transmission]] losses, among a number of [[tandem]]-connected items, such as equipment, cables, links, or trunks, in order to [[balance]] the performance of [[information transfer|communications]] circuits.  ''Synonym'' '''budgeting.''' 

'''2.''' In a [[telephone]] [[switching center]], the distribution or allocation of equipment or components proportionally among a number of functions, to provide a requisite [[grade of service]]. 

'''Source:''' from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]

In [[patient accounting]], the term '''proration''' refers to the act of taking money that is currently due from the insurance company and moving it to the patient, knowing that the dollar amount being moved is due from the patient as a [[deductible]], [[coinsurance]], or [[copayment]] amount.
 
